node.text:
By @grillhunters 
.
Have you ever had a grilled romaine salad before? If not, you’re in for a unique and delicious smoky surprise.

Here’s a list of ingredients for the marinade and salad. Full recipe with instruction is on the blog.

// Garlic & herbs marinade //
- 3/4 cup olive oil
- 1 lemon juice
- 1 tbsp basil, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp chives, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp rosemary, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp parsley, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp lemon zest
- 3 garlic cloves, minced
- 1/2 tsp chili powder
- 1 tsp salt
- 1 tsp black pepper

// Grilles Romaine Salad //
- 1 heart romaine lettuce cut in half lengthwise 
- ½ cup Parmesan cheese flakes
- 4 slice bacon grilled and crispy
- 4 tbsp olive oil extra virgin
- 1 tbsp kosher salt
- 1 lemon juice
- 1 tsp back pepper
- ½ lemon zest

#NomadGrills #grillhunters #grilledlettuce #grilledsalad #vealchop #grilledvealchops #smokedveal

node.text:
from Scratch! 🇲🇦😍🍆🍅🔥
This dish is a must and the flavors are amazing!
🕌: Fez, Morocco
🎥: @foodyfetish #foodyfetishoriginal 
Tag a Friend that would love this dish!👇🏼
.

Ingredients
* 1 large eggplant (peeled and chopped*)
* 4 large tomatoes (peeled, seeded and chopped)
* 3 cloves of garlic (finely chopped or pressed)
* 1/3 cup chopped fresh cilantro and parsley (mixed)
* 1 tablespoon paprika
* 1 tablespoon cumin
* 1 1/2 teaspoons salt
* 1/8 teaspoon cayenne pepper (optional)
* 1/4 cup olive oil
* 1/3 cup water
* Small wedge of lemon (optional)

To Make the Zaalouk:
* Mix all ingredients in a large, deep skillet or pot. Cover and simmer over medium to medium-high heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Adjust the heat if necessary to avoid burning the zaalouk.  Use a spoon or potato masher to crush and blend the tomatoes and eggplant. If you like, a small wedge of lemon can be added to the pan at this time. Continue simmering, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until the liquids are reduced and the zaalouk can be stirred into a heap in the center of the pan.

node.text:
Follow 👉 @bodysmartfitness for the best nutrition, mindset and fitness tips
.
Eat or pass this salad? 🥗 
This is one of those salads from @zestmylemon where leftovers came in handy! Air-fried chicken cutlet salad made with romaine lettuce 🥬, cherry tomatoes, hard boiled egg 🥚, avocado 🥑, a slice of crispy bacon 🥓 and homemade honey mustard dressing 🍯 and it was so darn delicious! I try to make chicken cutlets around here at least once a week both as part of a meal and for other purposes throughout the week. Not only are they good in a salad but also can be made into a quick chicken Parmesan, great on a sandwich or an easy chicken piccata to name a few. I make two different versions, air-fried or fried in oil the old fashioned way. Sometimes low carb sometimes not and here’s how I make them.⠀
.⠀
For the low carb gluten free version mix together 1 1/2 cups almond flour with 1 cup of grated Parmesan cheese along with 1 teaspoon dried oregano, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, 1 teaspoon onion powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon ground black pepper. In a separate bowl beat one egg with 1/4 cup of milk. Slice one pound of boneless skinless chicken breast into 1/4 inch thick pieces. Coat each chicken cutlet with egg mixture then into the dry mixture being sure to fully coat the chicken as much as possible. Spray the insides of your heated air fryer set to 400 F with oil spray and place the cutlets without crowding into the fryer. Make in batches if needed. Spray the tops of the coated chicken with more oil spray and cook for 15-20 minutes flipping half way through until your desired crispness.⠀
.⠀
For the full carb version replace the almond flour with 1 cup of all purpose flour and the Parmesan cheese with 2 cups of breadcrumbs, add the remaining ingredients and follow the same instructions as noted above.⠀
.⠀
If you don’t want to use an air-fryer heat 1/2 inch vegetable or avocado oil in a pan until hot but not smoking and cook the chicken cutlets in the hot oil flipping half way through until brown and crispy. 1 pound of chicken makes about 8 cutlets.

Follow 👉 @bodysmartfitness for the best nutrition, mindset and fitness tips
.
Eat or pass?! 🤤 

2-INGREDIENT DOUGH Blueberry Cinna-Rolls 🫐🥐 

Made in minutes and naturally sweetened with blueberries!…Made by lilsipper
.
For the dough:
1 cup *self rising flour (wheat, GF blend, or cassava)
1 cup plain greek yogurt (or *coconut yogurt)
.
*DIY self rising flour: mix 1 cup flour with 1 tsp baking soda and 1 tsp baking powder.
*If using coconut yogurt, you may have to add more flour if it's "runny" and not thick like greek.
.
Knead flour and yogurt to create a dough, roll out into long rods (grease your hands with coconut oil), sprinkle with cinnamon and wild blueberries (I used frozen), then roll-up and place in a baking dish. Bake at 350 F for 20 minutes. For the icing, I just drizzled melted coconut butter (different than oil) over the top. 

#blueberry #blueberries #cinnamonrolls #healthydesserts #ibs #guthealth #healthandwellness #healthyrecipes #healthyrecipe #coconut #coconutoil
